Sure! To write an if/then statement in C programming language, you need to use the if keyword followed by a condition in parentheses. If the condition is true, the code within the curly braces will be executed. For example:

```
if (age >= 18) {
  // Code to execute if the condition is true
}
```

In this example, the code within the curly braces will be executed if the age variable is greater than or equal to 18.
